none:
Originally ripped by Terminal Escape, posted on October 25, 2017 Description from Terminal Escape:
Who fukkn knows what planet this shit comes from, but this morning I present to you two doses of '80s Fast Times meets Valley Girl (seriously, you could put "No Heroes" up against Sembello's "Maniac" and no one would be the wiser). Antiquated synths and dated drum machines from both bands, while MAKING OUT WITH STRANGERS (who apparently feature a key member of SPLATTER WHORE and DIE WASTED on the keys) take a slightly darker and less Footloose approach. "Addicted To You(th)" is the soundtrack for me day, in case you were wondering. B.R.D.R. PRESENTS: DOMINATOR & MAKING OUT WITH STRANGERS
https://2.bp.blogspot.com/-77kLaZmLwlE/WfCVohkeiYI/AAAAAAAAR2k/FOkWFkt_x3cOR-KgeP3hcBLX6MfAL3UigCLcBGAs/s1600/BRDR%2Bcover.jpg https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zyYF-MiV3V4
